imdb.plot outline: When Aldrin returns from the States, everyone is as ecstatic as his grandfather. But his reason for going home is not because of his grandfather but his sister who is in an asylum. His vow is to take her away from their grandfather who caused the early death of their parents. To avenge for what happened to his family, Aldrin plans a final revenge and that's when Jenna comes into his life.

plot: When Aldrin returns from the States, everyone is as ecstatic as his grandfather. But his reason for going home is not because of his grandfather but his sister who is in an asylum. His vow is to take her away from their grandfather who caused the early death of their parents. To avenge for what happened to his family, Aldrin plans a final revenge and that's when Jenna comes into his life.::igma.tv

"Pati ba Pintig ng Puso?" an original Sharon Cuneta-Gabby Concepcion movie, is a story of a young, naive, servant named Jenna who falls in love with her master's grandson, Aldrin. Aldrin, who fled to the United States several years ago to escape his scheming grandfather, returns in the Griego mansion. The manipulative Don Griego is pleased that his grandson, whom he considers as the only heir of his wealth, will finally take over and be in charge of his business empire. Unknown to the rich aged man, Aldrin comes home to find out what really happened to his sister Mabelle, who now stays in an asylum, and not really to follow the orders of his domineering grandfather. The selfish and repressive Don Griego even arranges Aldrin to marry Agatha, a daughter of another wealthy businessman, to broaden their business empire. However, Aldrin, a free-spirited and defiant grandchild who is against all the system and policies of Don Griego, meets Jenna. Jenna is one of the maids in the mansion and is considered as Mabelle's best friend. And to spite his grandfather as well as assert his independence, Aldrin convinces Jenna to elope with him under the condition that their marriage will only be on papers. Aldrin believes marrying a servant is something Don Griego will never accept. He plans to use Jenna as his escape goat from being manipulated and controlled by his repressive grandfather. Since Jenna truly likes Aldrin, the servant agrees to marry her master. But will the domineering Don Griego easily yield to the marriage of his only grandson and heir of his wealth with a servant? What schemes will he take to make Jenna's life miserable? Will a one-sided love affair withstand the overwhelming defiance of the autocratic patriarch? Will Mabelle be able to come back to her senses and explain the reason why she suddenly stopped talking? And now that she is a Griego, will Jenna stand up against the old man just like her husband or will she allow Don Griego to run her life as well?::Anonymous
